{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838840378,"sessionID":"ses_287c31cefffevJ0bDyUJAaG0Mp","part":{"id":"prt_d783e45e0001uSjvVU1vz1Dqsf","messageID":"msg_d783d5e640013I1KGiT3HvH4aP","sessionID":"ses_287c31cefffevJ0bDyUJAaG0Mp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9e0eaa866faf4f6a8ed86409060fa080","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","content":"# AR-001 ŌĆö CRD AgentRuntime ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«Üõ╣ē Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n\n1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n\n### Type Definitions Required\n\n#### AgentRuntime\n\n```\nAgentRuntime\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Spec\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: targetPort)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Template (*SandboxTemplate, JSON: podTemplate, required)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, JSON: sessionTimeout, default: 15m)\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, JSON: maxSessionDuration, default: 8h)\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Status\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Conditions ([]metav1.Condition, optional)\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ List: AgentRuntimeList\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n\n```\nCodeInterpreter\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Spec\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ WarmPoolSize (*int32)\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Status\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Ready (*bool)\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ List: CodeInterpreterList\n```\n\n#### Supporting Types\n\n- `TargetPort`: Port configuration with optional pathPrefix/name, required port (uint32), protocol (HTTP|HTTPS)\n- `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n- `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n- `SandboxTemplate`: Labels, annotations, and embedded `corev1.PodSpec`\n- `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n- Webhook validation logic\n- CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n- client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n- HTTP API handlers (`pkg/api/`)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n| `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for embedded PodSpec in templates |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers to `client-go/` |\n| Workload Manager (`cmd/workload-manager`) | Reads CRD specs to create Sandbox/SandboxClaim |\n| Router (`cmd/router`) | May reference CRD types for routing logic |\n| E2E Tests | Validates CRD creation and behavior |\n| Helm Chart | Ships generated CRD YAML for installation |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Version Stability**: Using `v1alpha1` signals API instability; changes may break existing workloads\n- **Field Defaults**: Kubebuilder markers set defaults at CRD level; changing defaults affects existing unlabeled resources\n- **Enum Values**: Adding/removing enum values (ProtocolType, AuthModeType) requires CRD schema update\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Unstructured CRDs\n\n**Approach**: Define CRDs via raw YAML without Go types, consume via `dynamic.Client`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No code generation dependency; faster initial setup |\n| Cons | No type safety; no informer/lister generation; harder validation; no IDE support |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires typed clients for controller-runtime integration and test reliability.\n\n### Alternative 2: Single Unified CRD\n\n**Approach**: Merge AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter into one CRD with a `type` discriminator field.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Fewer CRDs; simpler client-go generation |\n| Cons | Schema complexity; divergent status fields (`ready` only for CodeInterpreter); authMode only applies to CodeInterpreter; warmPoolSize only for CodeInterpreter |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. The two CRDs serve distinct use cases with sufficiently different spec structures.\n\n### Alternative 3: External Template Reference\n\n**Approach**: Use `TemplateRef` (name/namespace) instead of embedded template.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reusable templates; smaller CRD instances |\n| Cons | Additional lookup step; template lifecycle complexity; no inline customization |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. Inline templates match agent-sandbox conventions and simplify the user experience. May consider as future extension.\n\n### Alternative 4: Duration as int64 seconds\n\n**Approach**: Use `int64` for timeout/duration fields instead of `metav1.Duration`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler serialization; no string parsing |\n| Cons | Non-standard K8s API; human readability reduced (e.g., \"8h\" vs 28800) |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. `metav1.Duration` follows Kubernetes API conventions and provides human-readable defaults (\"15m\", \"8h\").\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Kubebuilder marker typos | Run `make gen-crd` and verify output YAML |\n| Missing JSON tags | Use `golangci-lint` with tag-related rules |\n| PodSpec embedding complexity | Follow `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` patterns |\n| Code-generator version mismatch | Pin `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 per `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header via `make gen-copyright`\n2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions (e.g., `targetPort`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`)\n3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply `+kubebuilder:object:root`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:default`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`\n4. **Printer Columns**: Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` for `Age` column\n\n## References\n\n- Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n- agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n- Spec: `changes/AR-001/spec.md`\n- Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838840366,"end":1775838840375}}}}
